17:56.200 --> 17:57.760
And here are your hosts.

18:01.940 --> 18:09.960
This is Bill Vernon. And Daryl Lane. Science fiction author Kevin O'Donnell Jr.
has written many short stories plus six novels to date. Three of his novels form

18:09.960 --> 18:18.660
a series. The series is called The Journeys of McGill Feighan. And the three
installments are subtitled Caverns, Reefs, and Lava. McGill Feighan is a 21st

18:18.660 --> 18:26.740
century earthling who, at age four days, is swallowed by a mysterious, giant,
amoeba-like gastropod, which was sent by the even more mysterious, Far Being

18:27.260 --> 18:36.220
Retzglaran. The infant McGill remains in the gastropod precisely 71 hours and 24
minutes. Then he is discharged, and the gastropod leaves the earth with no

18:36.220 --> 18:45.400
comment. McGill seems to be a normal lad. At age five, however, it is discovered
that he has the flinger talent, the extremely rare ability to transmit people or

18:45.400 --> 18:54.220
objects instantaneously to distant destinations in the galaxy, providing the
total mass of any load doesn't exceed 918 kilograms. Young McGill is enrolled in

18:54.220 --> 19:02.140
the Flinger Academy, where he masters the art under the tutelage of experienced
flingers. Then at age 17, he is certified as a flinger. But since McGill is

19:02.140 --> 19:10.480
puzzled about the motive of the Far Being for having the gastropod swallow him
for three days, he vows to seek out the Far Being and ask him why. Another group

19:10.480 --> 19:17.960
is interested in McGill, too, the organization. They reason that if the Far
Being has something in store for McGill, then they want it, too. The stage is

19:17.960 --> 19:25.920
set. Young McGill is mastering flinging while simultaneously learning about such
things in life as romance, trying to live with the flinger bureaucracy, and

19:25.920 --> 19:34.220
searching for the Far Being. All the while, the sinister organization is after
him. The series is obviously humorous, but it's serious as well. Here O'Donnell

19:34.220 --> 19:50.320
comments on his intention for the series. Well, my primary intent in the McGill
fan series is to do something light, fast-paced, adventuresome, that nonetheless

19:50.320 --> 19:53.400
shows

19:53.400 --> 19:59.140
a person of incredible talent growing up. And the problems he faces.

20:01.940 --> 20:16.080
It's that aspect of it tends to take lower priority. I think the adventures of
McGill Feighan come first. I do want a book that people can sit down and read

20:16.080 --> 20:30.860
quickly and really enjoy. It's not a gloomy book. Bander Snatch and War of
Omission are sort of downbeat books. Mayflies is, in a way, upbeat, but it's

20:30.860 --> 20:45.540
got a lot of depressing stuff in it. Whereas McGill Feighan is, it's not. I do it
partly as a change of pace to write a book that just moves right along the start

20:45.540 --> 20:58.840
to finish. It has a lot of things happening. It's a very clear-cut hero who is
nonetheless human, has his problems. In the first book, Caverns, McGill takes

20:58.840 --> 21:08.740
charge of a Rangan egg which hatches in book two, Reefs. He names the young
reptilian Rangan Sam. And Sam becomes McGill's sidekick. Here O'Donnell comments

21:08.740 --> 21:19.400
on Sam's role. Poor Sam. I mean, he's going to grow up so mixed up. Because he's
being raised entirely on Earth. Well, except for their excursions off world. But

21:19.400 --> 21:31.940
he's being raised by a human being with very human values. But Sam is not human.
And when he gets to maturity, he's going to be, oh, heavens. From the tip of his

21:31.940 --> 21:41.960
nose to the tip of his tail, he's going to be about 15 feet long. And he's going
to stand about, oh, what, four and a half feet high at the shoulder? The back

21:41.960 --> 21:52.380
part of him. And his head will be, you know, pretty much about six feet off the
ground. I mean, he's going to be big. He's going to be very alien-looking. And

21:52.380 --> 22:06.500
he's going to have a lot of trouble because he's neither one nor the other. He's
not a Rangan. He knows nothing of Rangan culture. But he is not and can never be

22:06.500 --> 22:17.180
a human being. I see lots of interesting problems ahead for Sam. More on Kevin
O'Donnell Jr.'s The Journeys of McGill Feighan next time.

