23:53.660 --> 24:00.560
This is Daryl Lane and Bill Vernon. Kevin O'Donnell Jr.'s science fiction
series, The Journeys of McGill Feighan, is a highly popular adventure yarn

24:00.560 --> 24:07.420
featuring the young flinger, McGill Feighan, who, after having developed his
talent, is searching for the far being. Not only must young Feighan cope with his

24:07.420 --> 24:15.060
talent, and life in general, he must avoid being captured by the organization.
The series is humorous, but interspersed among the action and humor are the

24:15.060 --> 24:22.680
violent deaths of many of McGill's allies and friends, including his parents,
his lovers, and his roommates. We asked O'Donnell why he so freely dispatches

24:22.680 --> 24:35.060
with most of McGill's acquaintances. Part of that is cold calculation on my
part, that when you're writing a series, one of the real difficulties is

24:35.060 --> 24:42.140
convincing the reader that your hero is in danger. When you write one book,
there's no problem, because the reader doesn't know how it's going to come out.

24:42.280 --> 24:49.840
But when you have a series, the reader says, well, hey, look, you know, he's
been through 18 of these adventures now, and he's emerged unscathed from every

24:49.840 --> 25:00.300
one, so why worry? And, you know, the reader's emotional involvement in the
story is lessened. But when there is a real danger, when people near and dear to

25:00.300 --> 25:12.060
him are dying, and in some cases dying horribly, it brings the threat much
closer. It makes it much more plausible. And at this point, McGill has lost a

25:12.060 --> 25:24.280
lot of people who are very close to him. His parents, Nadia and Graystein, he's
going to lose more. You know, as I say, part of it is cold calculation, but part

25:24.280 --> 25:38.940
of it is also realistic appraisal of the situation fans in. He's got this
talent, he's got this mysterious link with this even more mysterious alien

25:38.940 --> 25:41.680
being, and he has people hot on his trail.

25:44.520 --> 25:56.560
And it streams, you know, readers' credibility to have not only Feighan, but all his
friends coming through safe and sound every time. You know, the organization,

25:57.440 --> 26:07.720
they may not be perfect, but they're not total amateurs, and they're going to be
striking real close to home. And they have so far in the first three books, and

26:07.720 --> 26:19.220
they'll continue to. McGill encounters several types of aliens on his journeys.
We ask O'Donnell for what purpose does he use alien characters in the series? In

26:19.220 --> 26:31.300
the fan series, I'm trying to make aliens who are comprehensible, and yet who
are not human. I really think when we run into alien species, and sooner or

26:31.300 --> 26:47.980
later we will, they will have traits which we recognize as traits that we have.
In Lava, I've got these religious fanatics running around. I suspect that any

26:47.980 --> 27:00.240
sentient race we encounter will, at least in one stage of their development,
have gone through an intensely religious period. It might still be religious

27:00.240 --> 27:13.200
today, if you can tell, but I think any sentient being has to wonder on its
origin, how it came to be, why it came to be, who created the universe. So, you

27:13.200 --> 27:18.060
know, I'm trying to, not to mirror humanity,

27:20.500 --> 27:30.840
but to suggest that there are alternates with which we can have traits,
attitudes in common. So far, O'Donnell has written three books in the McGill

27:30.840 --> 27:43.360
-Feighan series. Here's what O'Donnell said when we asked him if there would be
any more in the series. Yes, definitely. At the moment, it's a McGill story, and

27:43.360 --> 28:01.980
from his childhood, it's been published in Berkeley Showcase. There will be more
being books. At the moment, I'm saying seven more, and the series will end. So,

28:02.380 --> 28:09.800
it'll go out to at least ten. Kevin O'Donnell Jr. will keep us entertained with
the adventures of McGill Feighan for at least a while longer.

